t5409.text: If you’re in the same boat as me please pay attention to your mind and body! We can’t predict how our bodies will react in this situation so please don’t take your health for granted and be prepared that normal coping mechanisms may not be enough rn.

t5410.text: I’ve taken my reprieve from anxiety a bit for granted lately and that was a mistake. These aren’t normal times so why would my baseline be the same? I think I’m going to have to work harder to achieve the baseline I’m used to.

t5411.text: I’ve pretty much continued on business as usual, but..... it’s not usual. The widespread fear and uncertainty has definitely needled its way into my brain.

t5412.text: I think because I work from home anyway and am an introvert I haven’t been prioritizing my own everyday health as things have not been disrupted for me too badly by quarantining.

t5413.text: I’ve felt my anxiety creeping up over the past weeks and days and today is the worst it’s been in a long while. Not a full blown attack but having a lot of physical panic symptoms - racing heart, frantic thoughts, hives.

t5414.text: I’ve struggled with anxiety and panic attacks for about for the last 8 years. I got it under control with meds, therapy, and coping mechanisms, to the point where I haven’t had a panic attack in about 2 years.
